entry.title: Ukraine Proposes Neutral Status With Guarantees, but Zelensky Calls for More Western Help
entry.content: Kyiv outlined its demands during cease-fire talks with Russia, seeking binding security guarantees from the U.S. and some European countries, while the five-week-old Russian war on Ukraine raged on around the country.

entry.title: Russia Darkens Olympics' Bid for a Reset
entry.content: As venues shift to Western democracies in favorable time zones, organizers and broadcasters face prospect of less-competitive Games.
